  {
    "task": "Develop a 6-to-12-month recovery plan for the tourism sector",
    "owner": "Jason",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "We will travel locally, and potentially, we will travel intra-regionally, so staying within the region, but um to try and stand up the domestic travel market is going to be a long haul."
  },
  {
    "task": "Extend the wage subsidy for 20 weeks",
    "owner": "Jason",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "We have been lobbying nationally the government, and I think that's all sectors, not just tourism, around potentially extending the wage subsidy for 20 weeks cuz it will take a lot to restart um the tourism sector again."
  },
  {
    "task": "Partner with the civil defense network to provide welfare support",
    "owner": "Jason",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "We're also working with civil defense, we're also putting staff into there, as well."
  },
  {
    "task": "Develop a destination management plan",
    "owner": "Jason",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "We will now be developing a destination management plan and that'll be happening nationally as well to try and what we call transform tourism for the better."
  },
  {
    "task": "Review and revise the Statement of Intent (SOI)",
    "owner": "Mark Morgan",
    "deadline": "May",
    "evidence": "We have completed a very detailed 15-month forecast through to 30 June next year. That will form of course now part of the year one of the um of the SOI."
  },
  {
    "task": "Complete cost reductions in the business",
    "owner": "Mark Morgan",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "We've completed significant cost reductions in the business that's right across the business so that's um major cost reductions in our expense lines uh reductions uh pretty much across our business in terms of payroll uh anything up to a 20% reduction."
  },
  {
    "task": "Apply for and receive the government wage subsidy",
    "owner": "Mark Morgan",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "We applied for and received the government wage subsidy across the group."
  },
  {
    "task": "Join with Hamilton City to submit applications for Crown Infrastructure projects",
    "owner": "Mark Morgan",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "We have joined with um Hamilton City and um and I have spoken to uh Gary Dykes and others um around the obviously the Crown Infrastructure projects."
  },
  {
    "task": "Develop a clear business plan and set of objectives for FY21",
    "owner": "Mark Morgan",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "We have a clear set um of a clear business plan and a a clear set of objectives for FY21."
  },
  {
    "task": "Review and revise the Statement of Intent (SOI)",
    "owner": "Calvin",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "The organization really exists to do three things. First of all, to create effectiveness and efficiency gains for shareholders such as you."
  },
  {
    "task": "Advance strategic projects at pace",
    "owner": "Calvin",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "We are looking to be bolder, more disruptive to enable you to help you transform how you and other Waikato councils operate."
  },
  {
    "task": "Develop a re-examination of some of the work that LES is doing",
    "owner": "Calvin",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "I've asked for a re-examination of some of the work that we're doing to see whether we should stop doing it."
  },
  {
    "task": "Offer green financing to councils",
    "owner": "Andrew",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "We are intending to offer green financing to councils."
  },
  {
    "task": "Identify green projects and develop a certification process",
    "owner": "Andrew",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "We've actually got all the documents up and ready to go, but the issue is we're going to need councils to identify green projects."
  },
  {
    "task": "Develop protocols for managing external influences on staff health and safety",
    "owner": "Steve Shaw",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "We're working up some really good protocols around how to keep them all safe."
  }
]

